parameters: This Cucco is being held captive...\.\.\. probably to be shipped down for food,\. or its eggs.
This Cucco is being held captive...\.\.\. probably to be shipped down for food,\. or its eggs.
\n<???>Oh,\. a new face?\.\. And a kitten!\.\. How cute...
\n<???>Welcome to my "Anemone's Bloom",\. dear customer~\.\. I'm Anemone,\. the manager of this shop!
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Take this little gift,\. as a welcome to End City!\.\. This is our little mascot \c[18]pet\c[0]...
\n<Apothecary Anemone>The \ii[6] is a really special bug,\. very keen to find how Mana attaches itself to other living beings.\.\. At doing this,\. it knows its ways much better than any human!
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Most Divers use them \c[18]to remove things they can't normally part from\c[0]...
\n<Apothecary Anemone>They can be used to take off the \c[18]Relics\c[0] you've got on you!\.\. Aren't these little beetles amazing??\.\. *hanhanhan*~

\n<Apothecary Anemone>The Company doesn't permit anyone to traffic monsters outside their channels,\. even if its little guys like these,\. but we're allowed to hand out just one per customer,\. as a freebie!
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Make a good use of it~\.\. *hanhanhan*
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Any way we can assist you making this lovely town flourish~?
The air is filled with the smell of rotten fruit and chemicals.
You approach the witch to ask her what's the reason for that,\. but by the puzzled look on her face you can already tell she knows as much as you do.
\n<\n[1]>My nose is sensible,\. witch!\.\. You plan to knock me out with this foul stench?!
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\. Something's wrong here...\.\.\. a failed experiment,\. maybe?
\n<\n[3]>Come with me,\. cat.\.\. I want to get out of here as soon as possible,\. and you should too.
\n<\n[1]>Grrr...\.\.\. I shouldn't have let myself get involved...
The witch is waiting for you.\.\.
"In order to extract its core,\. inject the Melmos with poppies' extract and heat them up until they start boiling."
"Once drained of its ichor let it rest for..."
The rest of the paper is burned off.
\n<Bouncer>Humph...\.\.\. *coff*\.\. ...\.\.\. the witch is ahead,\. with the Boss.
This scene will be ready in one of the next builds!\.\. Thank you for playing up to this point!
\^\n<\n[3]>Here we are...\.\.\. She's just past here.\.\. When you'll meet her,\. I'd recommend you\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Huh?!\.\. "Here we are"?!\.\. You think you can play me like a stray?!
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\. You are as annoying as you're rough.
\n<\n[3]>When you've calmed down,\. come inside.\.\. She doesn't like cackles and commotions.
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. There was no need to get mad...\.\.\.
Noone could have expected a place like this,\. under the whole city's nose...
The room is dirty,\. and some of those muddy monsters you've met in the witch's basement are caged behind the counter.
An excessively well-dressed woman with an eyepatch sits behind the rough wood,\. rythmically tapping her long nails on its surface.
The witch has approached her.\.\. She seems to be doing the presentatious on your stead,\. but the woman hasn't looked at you once yet.
\n<\n[1]>You're digging yourself in deeper and deeper,\. witch.\.\. Now you'll have to do everything I say if you don't want me to snitch~
\n<\n[3]>Stop being ridicolous and come here.\.\. Our host has no time to lose...
\n<Apothecary Anemone>...\.\.\. silly girl~\.\. I thought you'd know better!\.\. Did I teach you about bringing strays home when you can barely take care of yourself~?
\n<Apothecary Anemone>You know...\.\.\. if anyone from the Company has noticed either of you...
\n<\n[3]>That!\.\. ...\.\.\. that didn't happen,\. Lady Anemone...\.\.\. I've been careful.
\n<\n[3]>This stray is too dumb to even think about scheming against us,\. trust me on this.
But the honcho isn't taking the words of the black-robed young girl for granted...\.\.\. her gaze is...\.\.\.
Slimy...\.\.\. dirty...\.\.\. despite the beautiful figure of Anemone,\. her enquiring gaze makes you feel strangely uncomfortable.
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. Ugh...\.\.\. \BST[7]let's just keep this thing going,\. ok?
\n<\n[1]>You just tell me what I have to do,\. then prepare for me the way down the Hole,\. I've got no time to lose in this city of yours.
\n<Apothecary Anemone>*hanhanhan*~\.\. Why are the two of you so tense?
\n<Apothecary Anemone>We're all friends here,\. allies...\.\.\. sisters,\. even!\.\. Isn't that right,\. Kaere?\.\. Didn't I treat you well until now?
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Of course I did,\. of course!\.\. *hanhanhan*!\.\. You've been under my wing since your father...\.\.\.
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Since you were but a child with no knowledge or experience as apothecary!\.\. Ain't I right,\. my child?
Something's going on here.\.\. You feel like is better to...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Listen,\. you two...\.\.\. I don't care what's going on here,\. let's just talk about the "plan"!\.\. You can sort things out between yourselves after that.
\n<Apothecary Anemone>*hanhan*~\.\. Certainly,\. let's talk business,\. before the witch uses her...\.\.\. *hmph*...\.\.\. sorcery on us~!
\n<\n[3]>...\.\.\. I...\.\.\. messed up,\. kind of.\.\. Let's just send this blackmailing cat down the Hole and forget about her.
\n<\n[3]>You explain her our line of work,\. "Boss"...
\n<Apothecary Anemone>As your sharp eyes surely have noticed!\.\. *hanhan~*\.\. ...\.\.\.
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Never the world has seen such a vast choice of expendable,\. mysterious,\. unique \c[18]lab rats\c[0]!
\n<Apothecary Anemone>*hanhanhan*~\.\. It takes just a few days for lesser monsters to mature into an adult,\. and some of them just multiply like it's nothing!
\n<Apothecary Anemone>Mana is surely nature's most powerful force,\. and it'd be a shame to not put it to good use,\. right?
\n<Apothecary Anemone>...\.\.\. but the Company...\.\.\. the nerve of them!\.\.\.
\n<Apothecary Anemone>They came to my Blooming boutique,\. acting all high and mighty!\.\. "Only the Company can run experiments on monsters!",\. they said!
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. let's get to the point,\. ok?
Anemone grabs you,\. coiling her dainty fingers around the fur on your arms.\.\. You didn't expect such inexcapable strength from a botanist...

Then you realize it may be you instead,\. getting weaker and weaker under her complete grasp.\.\. Her sweet breath is intoxicating.\.\. Sweet...\.\.\. too sweet...\.\.\. like rotten fruit.\\. You can't shake her off.
\n<Apothecary Anemone>You get me the \c[18]horn\c[0] of the monster that showed up inside the lake's \c[18]Shrine\c[0],\. and we'll have a deal.
